%S A394770 2,2,3,3,4,2,3,5,4,4,7,4,4,4,6,6,5,5,7,5,5,5,5,3,3,7,6,6,8,8,6,6,6,6,
%T A394770 8,8,8,8,7,7,9,9,9,7,7,7,7,10,9,9,9,9,8,8,10,10,10,10,8,8,8,8,11,11,
%U A394770 10,10,10,10,9,9,11,5,5,11,11,9,9,9,9,12,12
%N A394770 Smallest base b for which the average of the digits of n base b divided by b is the largest for any base b <= n.
%C A394770 Most terms arise from base b numbers of 2-digits, with a small portion of 3-digit numbers, and no observed >3-digit numbers.
%H A394770 Charles L. Hohn, <a href="/A394770/b394770.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A394770 Charles L. Hohn, <a href="/A394770/a394770.png">Graph of n, a(n) for n = 2..1000</a>
%e A394770 For n = 6: 6_2 = {1, 1, 0} and (1+1+0)/3/2 = 1/3, 6_3 = {2, 0} and (2+0)/2/3 = 1/3, 6_4 = {1, 2} and (1+2)/2/4 = 3/8, 6_5 = {1, 1} and (1+1)/2/5 = 1/5, 6_6 = {1, 0} and (1+0)/2/6 = 1/12; largest is 3/8, which first (and only) occurs for base 4, so a(6) = 4.
%o A394770 (PARI) a(n)={my(m=bmax=0); for(b=2, n, my(d=digits(n, b), s=sum(i=1, #d, d[i])/#d/b); if(s>m, m=s; bmax=b)); bmax}
%K A394770 nonn,base,new
%O A394770 2,1
%A A394770 _Charles L. Hohn_, Apr 01 2026
